node.text: I’ve been MIA after a 2+ week trip in South Africa working with @rhino911npo and had family in town for 2 weeks right after that but I can’t wait to share more about what I’ve been up to! I’m glad @olivela could jump on and chat wildlife conservation too and listen to me nerd out about my new book “World Wild Vet” (with @henryholtbooks ) 🤓👊

node.text: This is the first part of an intimate discussion with long-distance swimmer Ben Lecomte, documentary filmmaker Jared McGilliard, and ocean advocate and @seeker host @danniwashington about "The Swim," an incredible documentary following Ben's attempt to swim across the Pacific Ocean to raise awareness for ocean health. The film, the full discussion, and lots of other great bonus content is now streaming on @discoveryplus . Subscribe now to start streaming: http://bit.ly/dplus-ig

node.text:
Episode 8: Octopuses 🐙 

If there's one species on this planet I question could be an alien life form I think it would be the octopus! Watch our finale episode of season 1 "Tusks To Tails" to see what I mean 😋

FYI Octopuses think, feel, and smell with their arms — so scientists are using them as inspiration for innovations in material science, medicine, and soft robotics. 
@seeker

node.text:
Tomorrow morning YOU can experience the excitement & adrenaline of conservation work at home...(link in bio to join in 🙌)
My good buddy Dr. Joel @the_conservation_vet is working with the @blueskysociety to collar African elephants in the greater Kruger area and if you purchase tickets to see this process live you’re actually making a donation to help out wild elephants 😁. Collaring Wild elephants requires helicopters, intensive veterinary care, and lots of feet on the ground AKA it’s pretty expensive. The real value in collaring comes from the scientific, ecologically significant research to follow, helping prevent human:wildlife conflict (which is massively important regarding elephants), and influencing policy to better protect our wildlife & habitats. 
I put a link in my bio if you’d like to see this crazy process from home and help the elephants in doing so. 
And give Dr. Joel ( @the_conservation_vet ) here a “happy birthday” for me tomorrow because this guy is collaring elephants on his birthday 🥳🔥❗️
#elephant #wildlife #conservation #research #humanwildlifeconflict #policy #🌍 #🇿🇦

node.text:
“Long” turtles 😂… #snakes ❗️
Going to the creek was my FAV thing to do as a kid. Looking for neato reptiles, amphibians & insects was on my daily to-do list in those days. 
Seeking wildlife with my lil buddy, Bear and experiencing it thru his eyes brings me back to that childhood passion I’ve always had and makes these wildlife adventures special in new ways 🐸💫
It seems you don’t have to go far to show children our fascinating natural world. For those animal-loving kiddos our own back yards or local parks can get them as stoked as anything 🤓. 
@tim_diggs

node.text:
Willdife medicine is no joke and the potential for harm is even greater with the world’s biggest terrestrial animal, even when they’re sedated. And the risk potential is very high for our wildlife too. The individual spontaneously performing the African elephant assisted no-hands somersault surely realizes things could’ve been worse for him. 
#wildlife #medicine 🌍

We’re just tremendous
@conejovet

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Evan Antin 🐾 in Kabul, Afghanistan with @penfarthing, and @nowzadrescue. May be an image of 2 people, animal and text that says 'Ex-marine: I'm not leaving Kabul without my animal rescue staff By Marie Jackson BBC News 17 August 2021 Updated 3 hours ago NOWZAD Pen Farthing has rented a cargo plane to get the rescue animals out of the city A Royal Marine veteran, who founded an animal sanctuary in Kabul, has made an impassioned plea to the UK government to help his staff leave Afghanistan.'.

node.text:
@nowzadrescue 
Afghanistan’s fate has taken an even worse turn and my heart goes out to her people and the animals too. If you can help the Nowzad animal rescue in Kabul then please do. 
Our first world problems are on another planet compared to what faces those in Afghanistan. Thank you for your sympathy & support, link in bio 🇦🇫🙏
#nowzad @penfarthing #rescue

node.text:
This naughty elephant tho 😆🤍
#worldelephantday reminded me of this adorable/hilarious rescued elephant at the Uganda Wildlife Conservation Education Centre in Entebbe. This place was awesome btw and they host tons of school children most days to teach them about their native wildlife ☺️.
